cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.MA 

This paper proposes a refinement of the HYPE process algebra for modelling hybrid systems, introducing stochastic events. The paper discusses the semantics of the refined HYPE in terms of Transition-Driven Stochastic Hybrid Automata, which are a subset of a general class of stochastic processes termed Piecewise Deterministic Markov Processes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as the paper deals with modelling and semantics. Additionally, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) are also possible categories as the paper proposes a new approach to modelling hybrid systems.
